Glazed Maple-Pecan Oatmeal Scones
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 1/2 c rolled oats (4 1/2 oz) or quick oats
1/2 c chopped pecans
1/4 c whole milk
1/4 c heavy cream
1/4 c + 3 tbsp maple syrup
1 large egg
1 1/2 c unbleached ap flour (7 1/2 oz)
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp table salt
10 tbsp unsalted butter, cold, cut into 1/2" cubes
1/2 c confectioners' sugar

Adjust oven rack to middle position; heat oven to 375 F. Spread oats and pecans evenly on baking sheet and toast in oven until fragrant and lightly browned, 7-9 min; cool on wire rack. Increase oven temp to 450 F. Line second baking sheet with parchment paper. When oats and pecans are cooled, measure out 2 tbsp and set aside. Whisk milk, cream, 1/4 c maple, and egg in large measuring cup until incorporated; remove 1 tbsp to small bowl and reserve for glazing. Pulse flour, baking powder, sand salt in food processor until combined, ~4 1 s pulses. Scatter cold butter evenly over dry ingredients and pulse until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal, 12-14 1 s pulses. Transfer mixture to medium bowl; stir in coold oat/pecan mixture. Using rubber spatula, fold in liquid ingredients until large clumps form. Mix dough by hand in bowl until dough forms cohesive mass. Dust work surface with half of remaining pecan mixture, turn dough out onto work surface, and dust top with remainin oat/pecan mixture. Gently pat into 7" circle ~1" thick. Using bench scraper, cut dough into 8 wedges and set on parchment lined baking sheet, spacing them ~2" apart. Brush surface with reserved egg mixture and sprinkle with 1 tbsp sugar. Bake until golden brown, 12-14 min; cool on baking sheet on wire rack for 5 min, then move scones to rack to cool to room temp, ~30 min. When scones are cooled, whisk confectioners' sugar and 3 tbsp maple until combined; drizzle over scones. Serve.


Notes: Can sub half-and-half for milk/cream combo.
